                <h1>The Evolution of Emergency Medical Services: A Timeline</h1>
                <p>The history of Emergency Medical Services (EMS) traces back to the 1800s with horse-drawn ambulances. In the 1960s, EMS systems began evolving significantly, leading to advanced paramedic training and the introduction of emergency dispatch. Innovations continued into the 21st century with enhanced technology and mobile applications for improved patient care.</p>
